# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok the leaders of indonesia and east timor planned to meet friday to discuss a report that details atrocities committed by indonesia during its long occupation of the tiny nation .
# ::alignments
(p / plan-01
      :ARG0 (a / and
            :op1 (p2 / person
                  :ARG0-of (l / lead-02
                        :ARG1 (c / country
                              :name (n / name
                                    :op1 "Indonesia"))))
            :op2 (p3 / person
                  :ARG0-of (l2 / lead-02
                        :ARG1 (c2 / country-region
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "East"
                                    :op2 "Timor")))))
      :ARG1 (m / meet-03
            :ARG0 a
            :time (d / date-entity
                  :weekday (f / friday))
            :purpose (d2 / discuss-01
                  :ARG0 a
                  :ARG1 (r / report
                        :ARG0-of (d3 / detail-01
                              :ARG1 (a2 / atrocity
                                    :ARG1-of (c3 / commit-02
                                          :ARG0 c
                                          :time (o / occupy-01
                                                :ARG0 c
                                                :ARG1 c
                                                :ARG1-of (l3 / long-03)))))))))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok prime minister tony blair on wednesday condemned as `` brutal and wicked '' a wave of attacks in iraq that has killed dozens of people in recent days .
# ::alignments
(c / condemn-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Tony"
                  :op2 "Blair")
            :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG2 (m / minister
                        :mod (p2 / prime))))
      :ARG1 (w / wave-04
            :ARG1 (a / attack-01
                  :location (c2 / country
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "Iraq")))
            :ARG0-of (k / kill-01
                  :ARG1 (p3 / person
                        :quant (m2 / multiple
                              :op1 12))
                  :time (d / day
                        :mod (r / recent))))
      :ARG2 (a2 / and
            :op1 (b / brutal-02)
            :op2 (w2 / wicked))
      :time (w3 / wednesday))

# ::id 2 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok scientists scouring the area around stonehenge said thursday they have uncovered a circular structure only a few hundred meters -lrb- yards -rrb- from the world famous monument .
# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (s2 / scientist
            :ARG0-of (s3 / scour-02
                  :ARG1 (a / area
                        :location (a2 / around
                              :op1 (c / city
                                    :name (n / name
                                          :op1 "Stonehenge")))))
            :ARG1 (u / uncover-01
                  :ARG1 (s4 / structure
                        :mod (c2 / circular)
                        :location (r / relative-position
                              :op1 (m / monument
                                    :ARG1-of (f / fame-01
                                          :location (w / world)))
                              :quant (f2 / few
                                    :op1 (d / distance-quantity
                                          :quant 100
                                          :unit (m2 / meter))
                                    :mod (o / only))))
                  :time (d2 / date-entity
                        :weekday (t / thursday)))
            :ARG0-of u))

                        :name (n3 / name
                              :op1 "Kigali")))

                  :ARG0 (w / we)
                  :ARG1 (c4 / cooperate-01
                        :ARG0 (f / force

                              :quant 2)

                                    :name (n4 / name
                                          :op1 "DRC"))))))
      :ARG2 (p2 / publication
            :name (n5 / name
                  :op1 "Xinhua"))
      :time (ii2 / interview-01
            :ARG1 p
            :ARG2 p2

            :time (d3 / date-entity
                  :weekday (t3 / thursday)
                  :dayperiod (m / morning))))

                                                :op1 "al-Qaida"))

                                                      :op1 "Iraq")

                                          :location n4

                                                :ARG1 (m3 / militant
                                                      :quant 8))))))))
      :time (w / wednesday))

# ::id 8 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok concluding his first state visit , asian development bank -lrb- adb -rrb- president haruhiko kuroda thursday announced that the multilateral body was ready to raise development assistance to india in excess of #.# billion us dollars over the next three years , according to indo-asian news service .

      :ARG0 (p / person
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Haruhiko"
                  :op2 "Kuroda")
            :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG1 (o / organization
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "Development"
                              :op2 "Bank")
                        :mod (c / country
                              :name (n3 / name
                                    :op1 "Asia")))
                  :ARG2 (p2 / president)))
      :ARG1 (r / ready-02
            :ARG1 (b / body
                  :mod (m / multilateral))
            :ARG2 (r2 / raise-01
                  :ARG0 b
                  :ARG1 (a2 / assist-01
                        :ARG0 b
                        :ARG1 (c2 / country
                              :name (n4 / name
                                    :op1 "India"))
                        :ARG2 (d / develop-02)
                        :ARG1-of (ii / in-excess-of
                              :quant 1000000000
                              :unit (d2 / dollar
                                    :mod c2))))
            :time (a3 / after
                  :op1 (n5 / now)
                  :duration (t / temporal-quantity
                        :quant 3
                        :unit (y / year))))
      :time (d3 / date-entity
            :weekday (t2 / thursday))
      :ARG1-of (s / say-01
            :ARG0 (s2 / service
                  :mod (n6 / news)
                  :mod c))
      :ARG2-of (e / exclude-01
            :ARG1 (v / visit-01
                  :ARG0 p
                  :ARG1 (s3 / state)
                  :ord (o2 / ordinal-entity
                        :value 1))))

                        :value 2)
                  :mod (s / speedskating)))

            :ARG0 w
            :time (a / around
                  :op1 (l / lap
                        :mod (f / final)
                        :time (d2 / date-entity
                              :weekday (s2 / sunday))))

                  :ARG0 w

                              :op1 "###"

                        :poss (w3 / woman)))))

# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG1 (c / country
                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "China"))
                  :ARG2 (a / ambassador
                        :location (s2 / state
                              :location (c2 / center)
                              :mod (t / this)
                              :part-of (c3 / continent
                                    :name (n2 / name
                                          :op1 "Asia"))))))
      :ARG1 (o / open-01
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (b / border-01
                  :ARG1 c
                  :ARG2 (c4 / country
                        :name (n3 / name
                              :op1 "Tajikistan")
                        :ARG1-of (n4 / neighbor-01)))
            :location (m / may)
            :purpose (a2 / allow-01
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 (m2 / move-01
                        :ARG1 (a3 / and
                              :op1 (g / good)
                              :op2 (p2 / person)
                              :source c4)
                        :ARG1-of (f / free-04)
                        :path (a4 / across))))
      :time (w / wednesday))
